SIMPLE: errata
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Errata
<hw>Er*ra"ta</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[L.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>Plural of <er>erratum</er>. See
<er>Erratum</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A list of errors together with the corrections for
the errors, added as a separate page of a text prior to publication, or
as a separate sheet inserted into a printed text; <as>as, the
<er>errata</er> was added after the printing was
finished.</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><note> Although originally a plural word, the use of <er>errata</er>
as a singular word in second sense has become common.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Erratic</ent>⟦br⟧
